The http://www.dot.ca.gov/ California Department of Transportation (Caltrans) is a Department under the Governor of California which oversees Californias highways, various public airports, helipads, and intercity rail services. Caltrans has six primary programs: Aeronautics, Highway Transportation, Mass Transportation, Transportation Planning, Administration and the Equipment Service Center.

Locally, Caltrans repairs and maintains Interstate 80 and Highway 113 as well as the many overpasses and bridges which cross them. Caltrans also sponsors a pavement research facility in UCDs West Campus along with a variety of other cooperative arrangements with various University departments.

The current Caltrans director is Will Kempton who is overseen by the Secretary Dale Bonner who, in turn, serves at the pleasure of Governor Jerry Brown.

